| user_id2       | int         | FOREIGN KEY REFERENCES User(user_id) | Second user ID (FK)   |
| friendship_date| datetime    | NOT NULL                             | Friendship start date |
| PRIMARY KEY    | (user_id1, user_id2) | Composite PRIMARY KEY       | Composite key         |

The function should perform the following queries:
1. Use SELF-JOIN to find mutual friends (friends who share the same friend)
2. Use nested query to find users with more than N friends
3. Find friend-of-friend relationships (people connected through exactly one mutual friend)
4. Count friends per user and identify most connected users
5. Find users in the same city who are not yet friends (recommendation)

